        "header": "3Method",
        "images": [
            {
                "img": "https://arxiv.org/html/2604.11211/2604.11211v1/x2.png",
                "caption": "Figure 2:Overview of our real-time view interpolation framework.\nA lightweight Ghost-based backbone extracts multi-scale feature pyramids from the input images (left).\nA coarse-to-fine module then estimates depth and alpha for the target view using grouped correlations and residual refinement (center).\nFinally, a hierarchical fusion decoder aggregates projected features and synthesizes the novel RGB image (right).",
                "position": 613
            },
            {
                "img": "https://arxiv.org/html/2604.11211/2604.11211v1/x3.png",
                "caption": "Figure 3:Details on the Correlation Block (left) and Proj Block (right) fromFig.2.\nThe correlation block computes pairwise group correlations from depth-projected features and masks, processes them with depth proposals in a shared encoder–decoder, and refines the fused latents with the upsampled depth.\nThe projection block warps features using the current depth, predicts per-view weights, and aggregates them with a ConvNet into a latent representation.",
                "position": 695
            }
        ]
    },
